definition: above the head, located or originating from above, a hard return hitting the tennis ball above your head
details:
adverb
- above the head
- above your head
adjective
- located or originating from above
= example: located or originating from above
noun
- a hard return hitting the tennis ball above your head
= synonyms: smash
- (nautical) the top surface of an enclosed space on a ship
- a transparency for use with an overhead projector
- (computer science) the disk space required for information that is not data but is used for location and timing
= synonyms: disk overhead
- the expense of maintaining property, e.g., property taxes, utilities and insurance
= example: the expense of maintaining property, e.g., property taxes, utilities and insurance
= synonyms: operating expense, operating cost, budget items
- (computer science) the processing time required by a device prior to the execution of a command
= synonyms: command processing overhead time
